OL,7,FWriting for The Telegraph, the Labour
OL,8,Fpeer said the government's plans to
OL,9,Fabolish hereditary peers from
OL,10,Fparliament's upper chamber were "by no
OL,11,Fmeans the limit of the government's
OL,12,FLords reform ambitions".
OL,14,FThe House of Lords (Hereditary Peers)
OL,15,FBill, which is undergoing its final
OL,16,Fstages of parliamentary scrutiny, will
OL,17,Fabolish the 92 seats reserved for
OL,18,Fmembers of the upper chamber who are
OL,19,Fthere by right of birth.
