OL,7,FThere are currently 830 sitting
OL,8,Fmembers of the House of Lords, but no
OL,9,Fset limit on how many peers there
OL,10,Fshould be at any given time.
OL,12,FIn 1999, prior to reforms, membership
OL,13,Fof the House of Lords sat at nearly
OL,14,F1,200. This fell to around 700 after
OL,15,Fthe removal of hereditary peers'
OL,16,Fautomatic right to sit and vote.
