OL,7,FThe makeup of the House of Lords
OL,8,Fcurrently gives the Conservatives 285
OL,9,Fseats and Labour 209. The government
OL,10,Fhas however, committed in its
OL,11,Fmanifesto to reform the chamber with
OL,12,Fthe ultimate ambition of replacing it
OL,13,Faltogether.
OL,15,FIn her Telegraph article, Lady Smith
OL,16,Fsaid the Government was now looking to
OL,17,Fprogress further changes to the upper
OL,18,Fchamber.
