OL,5,Cenough
OL,7,FShe wrote: "Most peers agree the
OL,8,Fcurrent membership is too high and
OL,9,Fthat there are those who rarely
OL,10,Fattend. The committee will, in turn,
OL,11,Fbe able to look at what might be done
OL,12,Fwith or without legislation. I hope
OL,13,Fthe select committee will also
OL,14,Fanticipate any unintended
OL,15,Fconsequences."
OL,17,FWith plans to ensure peers retire at
OL,18,F80, the committee will meanwhile help
OL,19,Fto "avoid any possible cliff-edge
OL,20,Fmoment," she added.
